[2026-03-10T21:33:12Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015ZDbunJk2ByAxCfhffyCug","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Project Runs UI, Domain Types, and Time Formatting\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's everything you need to know about the Runs page UI, run display, domain types, and time-related functionality:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Runs Page UI Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**HTML Templates:**\n- **Runs List Page:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Displays paginated list of all runs with filtering by project\n- **Run Detail Page:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Shows individual run details, steps, logs, and child runs\n- **Layout Base:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Master template\n\n**HTTP Handlers (handler.go):**\n- `handleRunsList()` - HTML page serving\n- `handleRunDetail()` - HTML page serving  \n- `handleAPIRuns()` - JSON API endpoint for client-side polling (`/api/runs`)\n- `handleAPIRunDetail()` - JSON API endpoint for individual run detail (`/api/runs/{id}`)\n- **Port:** Uses `/runs` and `/api/runs` routes\n\n**Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Responsive design with dark mode support\n\n---\n\n### 2. **How Runs Are Currently Displayed**\n\n**Runs Table Columns (Template: runs.html, lines 14-49):**\n1. Run ID (linked)\n2. Title (truncated to 50 chars)\n3. Project (label)\n4. Workflow (name)\n5. Type (host or container)\n6. State (badge: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n7. **Started** - Uses `formatTime` template function\n8. **Completed** - Uses `formatTime` template function\n9. Container ID (shortened to 12 chars)\n10. Error Message (truncated to 80 chars)\n\n**Time Display Format:**\n- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` (e.g., `2026-02-26 14:30:00`)\n- Empty times display as blank strings\n- Server-side rendering uses `formatTime()` helper\n- Client-side polling also displays times in same format\n\n**Duration Display (Run Detail Page, run_detail.html):**\n- Uses `formatDuration()` template function\n- Format variations:\n  - Under 1 second: `500ms`\n  - Under 1 minute: `5.0s`\n  - Over 1 minute: `2m30s`\n\n**Run State Badges:**\n- Color coding via CSS classes: `badge-pending`, `badge-running`, `badge-succeeded`, `badge-failed`, `badge-cancelled`\n- Running badge has pulse animation\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Run Domain Types and Time Fields**\n\n**Domain Type:** `*domain.Run` (in `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, lines 31-47)\n\n**Time-Related Fields:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    StartedAt   time.Time      // When the run began\n    CompletedAt time.Time      // When the run finished\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\n**StepExecution Times:**\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time      // Step start\n    CompletedAt time.Time      // Step completion\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n\nfunc (e *StepExecution) Duration() time.Duration {\n    return e.CompletedAt.Sub(e.StartedAt)\n}\n```\n\n**Run Lifecycle Methods:**\n- `NewRun()` - Creates run with `StartedAt` and `CompletedAt` as zero values\n- `Start()` - Sets state to running, sets `StartedAt = time.Now()`\n- `Complete(state)` - Sets final state, sets `CompletedAt = time.Now()`\n- `Fail(msg)` - Sets failed state, sets `CompletedAt = time.Now()`\n- `RecordStepStart()` - Records `StartedAt` for each step\n- `RecordStepComplete()` - Records `CompletedAt` for each step\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Time Formatting Utilities**\n\n**Location:** Two implementations across the codebase\n\n#### **SQLite Storage (Internal):**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 431-444)\n\n```go\n// formatTime: Go time.Time → SQL storage (RFC3339Nano)\nfunc formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n    if t.IsZero() {\n        return \"\"\n    }\n    return t.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n}\n// Example output: \"2026-02-26T14:30:00.123456789Z\"\n\n// parseTime: SQL storage → Go time.Time (RFC3339Nano)\nfunc parseTime(s string) time.Time {\n    if s == \"\" {\n        return time.Time{}\n    }\n    t, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339Nano, s)\n    return t\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose:** Persistence - stores times with full nanosecond precision in SQLite\n\n#### **Web UI Formatting (Display):**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1293-1312)\n\n```go\n// formatTime: Display format for templates (human-readable)\nfunc formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n    if t.IsZero() {\n        return \"\"\n    }\n    return t.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04:05\")\n}\n// Example output: \"2026-02-26 14:30:00\"\n\n// formatDuration: Start and end times → readable duration\nfunc formatDuration(start, end time.Time) string {\n    if start.IsZero() || end.IsZero() {\n        return \"\"\n    }\n    d := end.Sub(start)\n    if d < time.Second {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%dms\", d.Milliseconds())\n    }\n    if d < time.Minute {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%.1fs\", d.Seconds())\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm%ds\", int(d.Minutes()), int(d.Seconds())%60)\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose:** UI display - converts times to user-friendly format\n\n---\n\n### 5. **API Response Format (JSON)**\n\n**Runs List API:** `/api/runs` returns `[]apiRun` (handler.go, lines 408-421)\n\n```go\ntype apiRun struct {\n    ID           string `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowName string `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n    ProjectDir   string `json:\"project_dir\"`\n    ProjectLabel string `json:\"project_label\"`\n    State        string `json:\"state\"`\n    StartedAt    string `json:\"started_at\"`      // Pre-formatted by formatTime()\n    CompletedAt  string `json:\"completed_at\"`    // Pre-formatted by formatTime()\n    ContainerID  string `json:\"container_id\"`\n    ErrorMessage string `json:\"error_message\"`\n    Title        string `json:\"title\"`\n    IsHost       bool   `json:\"is_host\"`\n    ParentRunID  string `json:\"parent_run_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Detail API:** `/api/runs/{id}` returns `apiRunDetail` with steps\n\n```go\ntype apiStep struct {\n    StepName    string `json:\"step_name\"`\n    Result      string `json:\"result\"`\n    StartedAt   string `json:\"started_at\"`   // Pre-formatted\n    CompletedAt string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n    Duration    string `json:\"duration\"`     // Pre-formatted\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Key Implementation Details**\n\n**Live Updates:**\n- Client-side polling every 3 seconds (runs.html, line 161)\n- Polling every 2 seconds for active run detail (run_detail.html, line 274)\n- Server-sent events (SSE) for live log streaming (`/api/runs/{id}/stream`)\n\n**Database Storage:**\n- SQLite with RFC3339Nano format (full precision)\n- Times stored in TEXT columns\n- Schema: `started_at TEXT`, `completed_at TEXT`\n\n**Parent-Child Run Hierarchies:**\n- `ParentRunID` field in domain.Run\n- Child runs displayed on parent detail page\n- API supports listing child runs via `ListChildRuns()`\n\n**Time Zone Handling:**\n- All times stored in UTC (via Go's time.Time standard)\n- Display format is human-readable without explicit TZ\n- RFC3339Nano includes TZ info for storage\n\n---\n\n### 7. **File Locations Summary**\n\n| Component | Location |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Run domain type | `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` |\n| Web handlers | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` |\n| HTML templates | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/*.html` |\n| CSS styling | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` |\n| SQLite store | `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` |\n| Time formatting (DB) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 431-444) |\n| Time formatting (UI) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1293-1312) |\n| Handler tests | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a125f72a226279b3f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59946\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 43946</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b04f5a15-d4ab-4e77-b440-71d43d500864","uuid":"81166a79-c2d2-4257-9064-15f1d562507f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the Cloche project to understand:\n1. Where the Runs page UI is implemented (look for HTML templates, handlers, web UI code)\n2. How runs are currently displayed (date format, duration, etc.)\n3. The Run domain types and what time fields are available (start time, end time, status)\n4. Any existing time formatting utilities\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/, cmd/, and any web/template directories. Look for patterns like \"runs\", \"status\", \"duration\", \"template\", \"html\", \"web\", \"ui\", \"handler\".","agentId":"a125f72a226279b3f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Project Runs UI, Domain Types, and Time Formatting\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's everything you need to know about the Runs page UI, run display, domain types, and time-related functionality:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Runs Page UI Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**HTML Templates:**\n- **Runs List Page:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Displays paginated list of all runs with filtering by project\n- **Run Detail Page:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Shows individual run details, steps, logs, and child runs\n- **Layout Base:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Master template\n\n**HTTP Handlers (handler.go):**\n- `handleRunsList()` - HTML page serving\n- `handleRun